title: Jackals spoil Royals' home opener, 7-2
text:
Large Text Jackals spoil Royals' home opener, 7-2 
win, 3-1 the reading royals played their home opener tonight...the team, shorthanded and it showed...- 2nd period. its already 4-1 elmira, and the jackals want more. spiro goulakos finds colin jacobs, who puts it past the diving net minder. elmira extends the lead to 5-1. jacobs had 2 goals tonight.- but the royals get one right back. riley armstrong takes it himself and beats the goalie. its now 5-2 elmira.- 3rd period. elmira has a 3-on-2. matt garbowsky deflects the pass across to taylor stefishen, who buries it in the net. that's stefishen's second goal of the game. its now 6-2 jackals....elmira spoils the royals home opener, big...7-2.
